--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
INFORMATION
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

This file lists changes made to the Ansible role. It follows semantic versioning
guidelines. The content is sorted in reverse chronological order and formatted
to allow easy grepping by scripts.

The fields are:
B: bug
C: change
E: enhancement
F: feature

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

* Version 2.1.1 (2020-10-30)
E: Simplify Ansible file header (ansible_managed)

* Version 2.1.0 (2020-07-24)
F: Add script 'zfs_trim-pools' to trim ZFS pools
B: Add missing cron file name for 'zfs_check-pools' and 'zfs_scrub-pools' scripts

* Version 2.0.0 (2020-07-03)
C: Remove option 'zfs_check_pools_interval'
C: Add option 'zfs_check_pools_minute' to specify interval (Default: '*/15')

* Version 1.0.0 (2020-06-29)
C: Redesign role to support SELinux

* Version 0.4.0 (2019-11-13)
C: Add support for Debian 10
C: Drop support for Debian 9

* Version 0.3.0 (2019-05-26)
F: Port role to Ansible 2.8

* Version 0.2.0 (2019-03-08)
F: Add support for monitoring via Prometheus node_exporter (textfile_collector)

* Version 0.1.3 (2019-01-24)
C: Rename option 'zfs_monitor_mail_recipient' to 'zfs_monitor_mail_from_address'
C: Rename option 'zfs_monitor_mail_sender' to 'zfs_monitor_mail_to_address'

* Version 0.1.2 (2019-01-22)
E: Improve script by throwing error message if script is executed interactively

* Version 0.1.1 (2019-01-21)
E: Improve script and reduce noise by removing echo command from alerting function

* Version 0.1.0 (2019-01-20)
F: Initial release
